 M http://src.chromium.org/viewvc/chrome/trunk/src/native_client/tools/modular-build/dirtree_test.py?r1=3771&amp;r2=3770&amp;pathrev=3771
 M http://src.chromium.org/viewvc/chrome/trunk/src/native_client/tools/modular-build/btarget.py?r1=3771&amp;r2=3770&amp;pathrev=3771

Modular build: Track identities of input tarballs and patches

This means that when the input tarballs/patches are changed, it will
cause the build system to re-unpack the source and trigger a rebuild
of the changed modules.

So this change fixes the build system to be properly incremental for
those modules that are stored as tarballs + patches -- currently
binutils, gcc and newlib, although we will switch these to use Git as
the canonical source at some point.

